                 The News Group Manager
                      Version 1.3

                 © Steve Collins 17/6/95

@{fg highlight}NGMan @{fg text}is an Arexx script that should hopefully make managing your Newsgroup
file a little easier.

                 - @{"  Features  " link "Features" 0} -
                 - @{"Requirements" link "Requirements" 0} -
                 - @{"Installation" link "Installation" 0} -
                 - @{"   Usage    " link "Usage" 0} -
                 - @{"  Options   " link "Options" 0} -
                 - @{"  History   " link "History" 0} -
                 - @{"  NGmerge & " link "Important" 0} -
                 - @{"   ALMan    " link "Important" 0} -
                 - @{" Important  " link "Important" 0} -
                 - @{"  Credits   " link "Credits" 0} -
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} FEATURES


- Easily @{"add" link "Add" 0}, @{"edit" link "Edit" 0} or @{"delete" link "Delete" 0} your current newsgroups using Reqtools
  requesters.

- @{"Browse" link "Browse" 0} the @{"active" link "Active news groups file" 0} newsgroup file, or your @{"new groups" link "New groups file" 0} file, and add
  groups by simply popping up a requester and entering a number.

- @{"Search" link "Search" 0} the @{"active" link "Active news groups file" 0} or @{"new groups" link "New groups file" 0} file with a keyword, and add any
  number of groups that come up as a match.

- Use an @{"ignore" link "Ignore Pattern" 0} pattern during the search to instruct NGMan to ignore
  certain entries.

- Re search the matched groups with a further keyword.

- @{"Sort" link "Sort" 0} your current newsgroups aplhabetically with a click of a button.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Features"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} REQUIREMENTS


                - Arexx
                - Rexxreqtools.library

                Rexxreqtools also requires the following-

                - Kickstart 2.04 or higher
                - rexxsyslib.library
                - reqtools.library, Version 38 or higher
                - diskfont.library
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Requirements"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} INSTALLATION


The only important alterations you may need to make to the script are as
follows-

1. Edit the @{bg shine}NEWS_DIR@{bg back} variable to point to the directory that contains
   your 'Newsgroup' file. The default is "UUlib:"

2. Edit the @{bg shine}NEWS_NAME@{bg back} variable to the name of your 'Newsgroup' file. The
   default is, surprisingly enough, 'Newsgroups'.

3. Edit the @{bg shine}NEW_DIR@{bg back} variable to point to the directory that contains
   you 'Newgroups' file. The default is "UUspool:"

4. Edit the @{bg shine}NEW_NAME@{bg back} variable to the name of your 'Newgroups' file. The
   default is, you guessed it, 'Newgroups'.

5. Edit the @{bg shine}ACTIVE_LIST@{bg back} variable to point to your list of active news
   groups. I have set the default as 'UUlib:active.newsgroups'

In addition to these settings there are a number of other @{"options" link "Options" 0} to enable or
disable certain features of @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text}.


 @{b}- NOTE -@{ub}

Be careful not to confuse your  @{fg fill}New@{fg text}groups  file with your @{fg fill}News@{fg text}group file and
vice versa.
@endnode

@node "Options" "Options"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Installation"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} OPTIONS


The following options may be altered to enable or disable certain features-

@{"IGNORE" link "Ignore Pattern" 0}   - The default ignore pattern.

@{"DEF_MAX" link "View" 0}  - The maximum number of entires to be displayed per page. I would
           recommend no more than 13 if you are using a non interlace screen
           (i.e. 640x256 etc) as more than that and the requesters may start
           to look a little odd. If you are using DBLPAL or an interlace
           screen this can be up to 30. Note however the higher the number
           the slower the redraws.

@{"DEF_DAYS" link "Add" 0} - Default days to keep messages. If you add a newsgroup it will
           automatically be set to this figure.

@{"CONFIRM" link "Delete" 0}  - CONFIRM = 1 - Confirm any deletions
           CONFIRM = 0 - Disabled

@{"SORT_NEW" link "New groups file" 0} - If = 1 then groups found in the new groups file will be sorted
           alphabetically when @{"BROWSED" link "Browse" 0}. If = 0 groups will be displayed as
           found.

SCREEN   - Rexxreqtools will try to open it's requesters on the screen that
           called the script. Setting this to a public screen name will try
           to overide it. Be warned, it is case sensitive.

REQWIDTH - Prevents very long entries from running over the end of the
           requesters. Any characters over this figure will be replaced with
           '>>>'.

PROGTXT  - Just a small modification. If set to 1 the search progress window
           will show some info on the current KEYWORD and @{"IGNORE" link "Ignore Pattern" 0} pattern in
           use. If set to 0 it will be disabled.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "   Usage    "
@next "Add"
@prev "Options"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} USEAGE


The first requester that appears will look something like this-


   NGMan 1.3

       - 4 Newsgroups found in UUlib:Newsgroups-

 @{"View" link "View" 0}   @{"Add" link "Add" 0}   @{"Browse" link "Browse" 0}   @{"Search" link "Search" 0}   @{"About" link "Important" 0}   @{"Save & Exit" link "Save & Exit" 0}   @{"Abort" link "Abort" 0}
@endnode

@node "View" "View"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} VIEW


Selecting view from the initial requester will present you with the current
newsgroup requester.

If you have any current newsgroups in your Newsgroup file they will be listed
alongside an index number. Depending on how many groups are found and what
figure you have set the @{"DEF_MAX" link "Options" 0} variable at, there may be more than one page.
The keys at the extreme ends of the button bank will enable you to page back
and forward through the list. If all your current groups fit on one page then
these buttons will be ghosted and disabled.

Example..

  NGMan 1.3

       (1) comp.sys.amiga.announce 2
       (2) demon.ip.support.amiga 2
       (3) demon.announce 2
       (4) comp.sys.amiga.programmer 2
       (5) alt.sex.bestiality.hamster.duct-tape 7

              5 shown, 0 remaining

  @{">>" link "Page forward" 0}    @{"Leave" link "Usage" 0}   @{"Edit" link "Edit" 0}  @{"Delete" link "Delete" 0}   @{"Sort" link "Sort" 0}   @{"Add" link "Add" 0}   @{"<<" link "Page back" 0}
@endnode

@node "Add" "add"
@prev "Features"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} ADD


Selecting ADD from the initial requester or the current newsgroup requester
will enable you to enter a new news group manually. Just enter the full name
of the news group followed by the number of days you wish to keep the
messages. Just pressing return will cause the 'days to keep' to be set to your
@{"default" link "Options" 0} setting.

BE WARNED..

News groups are case sensitive. Just one incorrect character and you will fail
to link to the news group.
@endnode

@node "Edit" "edit"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} EDIT


Selecting EDIT from the current news group list window will allow you to edit
the entry.

First you will be presented with a requester to edit the name of the group
followed by the days to keep. Simply pressing return will cause the original
value to be used.
@endnode

@node "Delete" "delete"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} DELETE


Selecting DELETE from the current news group list window will allow you to
delete a cuurent news group from your Newsgroup file.

You will be presented with a requester showing your current groups listed
along side an index number. Enter the number of the group you wish to delete.

Setting the CONFIRM variable to '1' in the script will result in a
confirmation requester enabling you to cancel deletion. Set the variable to
'0' to disable the requester.
@endnode

@node "Browse" "Browse"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} BROWSE


Selecting BROWSE will enable you to 'page' through the entries in either your
@{"active" link "Active news groups file" 0} news group list, your @{"new" link "New groups file" 0} groups list or the @{"hitlist" link "Hitlist" 0}.

The requester will look something like this..

  NGMan 1.3

          Browsing active newsgroups
          PAGE 1

          1) linux.jobs
          2) tw.bbs.sports.volleyball
          3) tw.bbs.alumni.kavalan
          4) fj.rec.games.mahjong
          5) linux.dev.raid
          6) chi.politics
          7) chi.internet
          8) rec.music.makers.dulcimer
          9) alt.uniwue.infoIII
          10) alt.marketplace.funky-stuff.forsale


          @{">>" link "Page forward" 0}   @{" ADD " link "" 0}  @{" Leave " link "Usage" 0}   @{"<<" link "Page back" 0}


If there are more than one page of entries you can move back and forward
through the list using  >>  or  <<  , or the <CR> and <Esc> keys.

Each entry in the list will be shown alongside an index number. To add any of
the listed groups just press @{" add " link "" 0} and enter the index of the group you wish
to add to your current @{"NewsGroups" link "Newsgroups file" 0} file.
@endnode

@node "Search" "Search"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} SEARCH


Selecting search will present a requester giving you three choices of files to
search.


 NGMan 1.3


     Search which file..

   @{"Active" link "Active news groups file" 0}   @{"Hitlist" link "Hitlist" 0}   @{"New" link "New groups file" 0}


You will then be prompted to enter a keyword. Only one keyword may be used,
any additional words will be ignored. The Active file is the default response
and can be selected by pressing <CR>.

Once you have entered the keyword, you will be asked to confirm the search and
will also be given an opportunity to edit either the keyword or the ignore
pattern.

Once started the progress indicator will show the character '*' if a match is
found, and '-' if a match is found but subsequentley ignored when compared to
the @{"ignore" link "Ignore Pattern" 0} pattern.

Pressing 'Control C' at anytime will abort the search, still enabling you to
view any matches found up to that point.
@endnode

@node "Hitlist" "hitlist"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} THE HITLIST


The hitlist is a file of matched entries created by the @{"search" link "Search" 0} option, and is
held in your T: directory. Immediately after a succesful search it is renamed
hitlist.tmp.old and is then available for further searching.
@endnode

@node "Ignore Pattern" "The Ignore Pattern"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} THE IGNORE PATTERN


The ignore pattern is a series of keywords used by NGMan during the @{"search" link "Search" 0}
routine. Any entries matched during the search will be compared to each
element of the Ignore pattern, and if any are found to match the entry will be
ignored.

This can be very useful for filtering out usenet groups for which you may have
no interest in. For example as an Amiga user you might like to set the default
ignore pattern to '.atari .acorn .ibm' ;)

Obviously the larger the ignore pattern the slower the search, but the ignore
routine is only called when a match is found. Two or three entries will only
have a mild effect on the speed of the search.

The ignore pattern can be changed at any time via the search requester. If you
have just carried out a search using an ignore pattern it makes sense to
disable or alter the ignore pattern if you then search the @{"hitlist" link "Hitlist" 0}. (As all
the entries in the hitlist will have already been checked against the current
ignore pattern)
@endnode

@node "Sort" "Sort"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} SORT


Selecting SORT will simply sort your current news groups aplhabetically.
@endnode

@node "Page forward" ">>"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} PAGE FORWARD


The @{fg highlight}>>@{fg text} button will page you forward through the list of entries. Pressing @{fg fill}<CR>@{fg text}
(that's CURSOR RETURN) will have the same effect.

If you are on the last page, or there is only one page the button will be
displayed as @{" - " link "Ghosted Buttons" 0} .
@endnode

@node "Page back" "<<"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} PAGE BACK


The @{fg highlight}<<@{fg text} button will page you back through the list of entries. Pressing the
@{fg fill}<Esc>@{fg text} key will have the same effect.

If you are on the first page, or there is only one page the button will be
displayed as @{" - " link "Ghosted Buttons" 0} .
@endnode

@node "Ghosted Buttons" "Ghosted Buttons"
                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} GHOSTED BUTTONS


If the function of a button is disabled it will be displayed as @{" - " link "" 0} .
@endnode

@node "Save & Exit" "Save & Exit"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} SAVE & EXIT


Selecting Save & Exit will save all changes, by copying the temporary file
held in your T: directory over the original Newsgroup file, and then exit.
@endnode

@node "Abort" "Abort"
                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} ABORT


Exit @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} and ignore any changes that may have been made.
@endnode

@node "Newsgroups file" "Newsgroup file"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} NEWSGROUPS FILE


The @{fg fill}News@{fg text}groups file instructs the NNTP transfer routine as to which USENET
groups it should collect news from. It will usually be found in UUlib:
@endnode

@node "Active news groups file" "Active newsgroups file"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} ACTIVE NEWSGROUPS FILE


This is a file, available by FTP from Demon, which lists all available active
newsgroups.

                 'ftp.demon.co.uk       /pub/news/active'
@endnode

@node "New groups file" "New groups file"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} NEW GROUPS FILE


If you use the Arexx script @{"Plink" link "Plink" 0}, instead of the original 'link' script, you
will probably be aware that it can be configured to save a list of any new
news groups each time you 'Plink up'. @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} can @{"browse" link "Browse" 0} this list and allow you
to easily @{"add" link "Add" 0} any groups from the list.

Otherwise you may have configured your setup to save information of New groups
to a seperate file. Providing this is either just a straight list of groups,
or , like the Plink type, just a list of groups with a date/time line in the
format '16/06/95-06:38:56' then @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} will be able to use it.

If you save your newgroups in a different format, let me know and I'll amend
the script.

By default the file @{fg fill}New@{fg text}Groups can usually be found in UUspool:
@endnode

@node "Plink" "Plink - What is it"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} PLINK
      (Plink by Phil Stewart-Jones / phil@curve.demon.co.uk)

 "Plink 2.1 is a ARexx dial-up program, designed specifically for use with
  AmiTCP-DIS installed systems, but which should be adaptable for any dial
  up system using AmiTCP.  It can be dropped in in place of the original
  "link" program, or indeed in place of Plink 1.0."

  Plink is available via FTP from Demon "plink21.lha  amitcp/utils"
@endnode

@node "Important" "Important"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} IMPORTANT


@{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} is freeware. Feel free to use it, distribute it or hack it about to your
hearts content, but I cannot be held responsible for any damage or loss caused
through it's use, you use it at your own risk.

However if you do find @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} useful then, eternal optimist that I am, I am
offering the opportunity to @{fg highlight}r@{fg text}e@{fg fill}g@{fg text}i@{fg highlight}s@{fg text}t@{fg fill}e@{fg text}r, yes that's right @{fg highlight}r@{fg text}e@{fg fill}g@{fg text}i@{fg highlight}s@{fg text}t@{fg fill}e@{fg text}r.

Gasp! Shock! Horror! Register? An Arexx script? Who the @{i}hell@{ui} does this guy
think he is?!

Well hold on a second. All I'm asking for is one measley pound. Just sit and
think for a second about what you can get for a pound these days? A bag of
chips.... a couple of minutes on a mobile phone.... 2 succesful connections to
Demon on a weekday evening... And just look at what you'll get for your
quid..

In return I will forward you the @{i}latest@{ui} versions of @{"NGmerge" link "NGmerge" 0} and @{"ALMan" link "ALMan" 0}. Note
these versions are NOT freeware, and will not be placed in the Public Domain.
I will also email you direct any future releases of @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} before anyone else
gets there grubby hands on them.

So, on the assumption that anyone has actually got this far how about sticking
a shiny gold coin in an envelope and winging it towards-

                      Steve Collins
                      125 St.Johns Road
                      Tunbridge Wells
                      Kent TN4 9UG

.. include your email address and ALMan and NGmerge will be on there way to
you quicker than a very very quick thing.

Even if you don't feel like coughing up, still drop me a line if you have any
suggestions, critiscisms, bug reports etc... just don't expect a reply..;))
only kidding!

    email: steve@stuffs.demon.co.uk
    WWW:   http://metro.turnpike.net/C/cheeky/INDEX.HTML

The latest version of @{fg highlight}NGMan@{fg text} can always be obtained from my mailserver. Just
write to 'mailserver@stuffs.demon.co.uk' with the text 'GET NGMan.lha'. All I
ask is that if you request it from my mailserver, please drop me line at the
same time.

I will also upload it to both the Demon and Aminet ftp sites.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@prev "Important"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} HISTORY


1.0 - Simple ADD/REMOVE/DELETE options.

1.1 - Added @{"SEARCH" link "" 0} routine and tidied up error checking etc.

1.2 - Added @{"IGNORE" link "Options" 0} pattern option, and search progress indicator.

1.3 - Completely rewrote entire script..

- Default responses made much more 'intuitive'

- Added @{"BROWSE" link "" 0} option.

- Now possible to page back and forward through pages of entries
  using just the @{"<CR>" link "Page forward" 0} and @{"<Esc>" link "Page back" 0} keys.

- @{"Control-C" link "Search" 16} now aborts search routine.

- Now handles very long entries correctly via @{"REQWIDTH" link "Options" 0} variable

- Added option to sort your current newsgroups alphabetically

- Added handling of a @{"Newgroups" link "New groups file" 0} file, including the Newgroups file created by
  @{"Plink" link "Plink" 0}.

- All adding/deleting/editing is now carried out on a copy of @{"NewsGroups" link "Newsgroups file" 0}
  held in T:

- @{"Initial requester" link "Usage" 0} now shows total changes made.

- Now possible to search the @{"Hotlist" link "Hitlist" 0} created from a previous search.
@endnode

@node "NGmerge" "NGmerge"
                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} NGMERGE


@{fg highlight}NGmerge@{fg text} is an Arexx script that will automatically merge your @{"Newgroups" link "New groups file" 0} file
with your @{"Active" link "Active news groups file" 0} newsgroups file and then re-sort it alphabetically.
@endnode

@node "ALMan" "ALMan"

                   @{fg highlight} NGMan 1.3@{fg text} ALMan


@{fg highlight}ALMan@{fg text} is an ARexx script which will enable you to manage your mail Aliases in
the same way NGMan manages Newsgroups.
@endnode

